  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Provision of essential WASH, Protection and Education opportunities for crisis-affected, displaced children and communities in Kachin and northern Shan States</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Building on previous humanitarian assistance in partnership with local and international actors, the project aims to ensure reliable access to quality and relevant basic services for newly displaced children and their communities in 13 IDP camps in 3 townships in Kachin State, and in 2 camps in 1 township in northern Shan State. Three types of interventions are proposed:

(1) Provision of WASH facilities and services. Community latrines, hand washing and drinking water stations, and emergency bathing places are constructed. Community hygiene promotion activities, led by volunteers, are planned, with workshop and IEC materials. Hygiene kits are distributed.
(2) Provision of protection (EMDR Therapy) and child protection (referral and awareness) services for crisis-affected adults and children, focused on awareness raising and outreach sessions and support activities on the psychosocial impact of displacement. 
(3) Provision of non-formal education opportunities for children in Grades 1 through 9. Temporary Learning Spaces (TLS) are constructed, with WASH facilities (latrines, drinking and hand washing stations), fitted with furniture and equipped with school kits. Student kits for primary and middle school level children are provided, as well as salaries for teachers.

The project seeks to holistically address the differing needs of conflict-affected women, men, boys and girls, as well as other vulnerable groups, to ensure that no one is excluded.</narrative>
  </description>
